19:38.351 --> 19:40.091
Elizabeth Taylor?
Maybe.

19:40.135 --> 19:41.484
Let's see what we have.

19:45.662 --> 19:47.316
Am I on the phone? No...

19:52.713 --> 19:55.150
Nope.
No Elizabeth Taylor.

19:55.194 --> 19:56.847
- Hi.
- Hi.

19:56.891 --> 19:59.067
No, I don't have
anything in stock.

19:59.110 --> 20:00.895
Can I get something for you?

20:00.938 --> 20:03.724
No, I didn't realize
we couldn't browse.

20:03.767 --> 20:05.987
- Yeah, sorry.
- Judy.

20:06.030 --> 20:07.815
I put aside
"Girl, Woman, Other."

20:07.858 --> 20:09.425
- I just called you.
- Judy, okay, hold on.

20:11.427 --> 20:14.082
Do you want me to get you
a copy of the Jane Austen?

20:14.125 --> 20:15.431
No, because
I won't be here.

20:15.475 --> 20:16.954
That would be great.

20:25.746 --> 20:27.313
Monica.

20:27.356 --> 20:28.792
Oh, Monica...

20:30.229 --> 20:32.013
And...

20:35.016 --> 20:36.539
[humming softly]

20:36.583 --> 20:39.194
- [beep]
- That's it.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.891
Expiration?

20:46.767 --> 20:48.551
What's the secret number?

20:53.034 --> 20:54.601
Four digits.

21:00.563 --> 21:01.956
And the billing zip code?

21:03.392 --> 21:05.002
The billing zip code.

21:06.395 --> 21:08.179
Okay, Judy,
I'm gonna ask you

21:08.223 --> 21:11.313
to step on the sidewalk
while I put it on the stool.

21:11.357 --> 21:14.708
That way we don't inadvertently
dance with each other.

21:14.751 --> 21:16.405
- Thank you so much.
- Okay, thank you.

21:16.449 --> 21:17.928
Would you like
a bag for that?

21:17.972 --> 21:19.887
- It's a nice procedure.
- Thank you.

21:21.671 --> 21:24.239
- Mike!
- Yes.

21:24.283 --> 21:26.763
Hi.
[laughing]

21:26.807 --> 21:29.157
I need some...
legal pads.

21:29.200 --> 21:30.724
Legal pads.
The yellow pad.

21:30.767 --> 21:32.247
Yep, 8 1/2 by 11?

21:32.291 --> 21:33.857
- Yeah.
- Or long...

21:33.901 --> 21:35.250
- No, yeah.
- Eight and a half by 11.

21:35.294 --> 21:37.600
Like three of them.
Thank you.

21:41.604 --> 21:44.825
You know, if I stop
to think about...

21:44.868 --> 21:48.959
uh... finances...

21:52.833 --> 21:56.184
or the future,
when we're not gonna

21:56.227 --> 21:58.186
want to have the door open,
when it's gonna--

21:58.229 --> 22:00.884
when it's gonna be dark
at 4:00 in the afternoon,

22:00.928 --> 22:03.757
I... my mind stops.

22:05.411 --> 22:08.588
I can't, um...
can't imagine.

22:15.377 --> 22:18.380
[soft guitar]

22:28.999 --> 22:31.611
- Hi.
- Hi.

22:31.654 --> 22:33.395
Give me a... mystery,

22:33.439 --> 22:35.354
some light reading
for the summer.

22:35.397 --> 22:38.444
Even in a paperback,
that's okay with me.

22:38.487 --> 22:40.097
How about you?

22:40.141 --> 22:42.404
Uh, I came up
with my books, thank you.

22:42.448 --> 22:43.797
- Oh!
- I did.

22:43.840 --> 22:45.494
A lot you care about me.

22:45.538 --> 22:47.322
Actually, I do.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.280
[man] Something,
I don't care if it was

22:49.324 --> 22:51.195
on the bestseller list.
Something you like.

22:54.590 --> 22:55.896
Let's see.

22:59.378 --> 23:01.597
Let's see.
What can we get this guy?

23:03.947 --> 23:05.645
"The Black-Eyed Blonde."

23:05.688 --> 23:07.473
Oh, I think
I used to date her.

23:07.516 --> 23:08.909
Okay, how much?

23:10.693 --> 23:13.087
It's credit card only,
I'll tell you in a minute.

23:13.130 --> 23:14.741
- Credit card only.
- Credit card only.

23:24.533 --> 23:26.056
No, no, no, no.

23:26.100 --> 23:28.015
I need you
to read it to me.

23:30.017 --> 23:32.062
I'm taking my mask off,

23:32.106 --> 23:34.456
but the glass should be
good protection.

23:36.066 --> 23:39.069
[reciting digits]

23:40.157 --> 23:42.203
Get outta here.
Back up.

23:42.246 --> 23:43.987
[muffled chatter]

23:46.512 --> 23:48.296
Ah... no, no, no.

23:48.339 --> 23:50.472
I'm going to put it
on that stool over there.

23:50.516 --> 23:52.213
- And Norman?
- Yes.

23:52.256 --> 23:54.563
- I want you to tie your shoe.
- Good idea.

23:54.607 --> 23:56.435
Yeah, well,
I just stepped on a lace now.

23:56.478 --> 23:59.350
Matt, The Bookloft
in Great Barrington closed?

23:59.394 --> 24:01.091
- It closed?
- Yeah, oh, you didn't know?

24:01.135 --> 24:03.442
No, no, they moved.

24:03.485 --> 24:05.618
- Oh, where did they move to?
- They're on State Road.

24:10.492 --> 24:12.712
I'm on credit hold
with Simon & Schuster

24:12.755 --> 24:14.235
because I owe 'em
too much money.

24:14.278 --> 24:15.889
I don't have enough money
to pay 'em

24:15.932 --> 24:18.326
right now.

24:18.369 --> 24:21.198
Peter, this is Matt.
Peter, I just sent an order

24:21.242 --> 24:22.939
into Taylor
& Francis yesterday,

24:22.983 --> 24:25.115
but I have an old--
I have four old invoices

24:25.159 --> 24:27.248
that I wanted to pay.

24:27.291 --> 24:29.337
And I wanted
to make sure that...

24:29.380 --> 24:31.382
that you would let
the order go through.

24:31.426 --> 24:34.516
I'm going to send you
a check for...

24:34.560 --> 24:36.866
I have it right here
on the other desk.

24:36.910 --> 24:38.781
So, I'm up a tree?

24:38.825 --> 24:41.305
Do I... sacrifice everything

24:41.349 --> 24:45.222
and... pay
Simon & Schuster $3600

24:45.266 --> 24:48.225
so I can buy one book
for this person?

24:48.269 --> 24:49.923
I'm going to hold off on that.

24:49.966 --> 24:53.100
Just because I need
to pay other people too.

24:58.061 --> 25:00.237
"All the Colors."

25:00.281 --> 25:02.413
Two copies.
"All the Colors We Are."

25:02.457 --> 25:04.111
How-- whoa!

25:08.115 --> 25:12.293
"Union."
Two copies at $28.

25:12.336 --> 25:14.643
What is "Union?"
A democrat and republican

25:14.687 --> 25:16.297
search for common ground.

25:17.777 --> 25:19.387
[phone ringing]

25:19.430 --> 25:22.216
Hello, Bookstore.
There you are.

25:23.609 --> 25:27.438
It's... this all melds
into psychology.

25:30.746 --> 25:32.269
Or does it?

25:36.230 --> 25:38.275
Another one.

25:43.498 --> 25:44.891
"I am discontented.

25:44.934 --> 25:46.719
I want something
I do not have.

25:46.762 --> 25:49.199
There must be more to life
than having everything.

25:49.243 --> 25:51.201
In the middle of the night,
she packed everything

25:51.245 --> 25:53.029
into a black leather bag
with gold buckles

25:53.073 --> 25:54.596
and looked out
of her favorite window

25:54.640 --> 25:56.467
for the last time.
'You have everything,'

25:56.511 --> 25:57.730
said the potted plant
that happened to be

25:57.773 --> 25:59.340
looking out
of the same window.

25:59.383 --> 26:01.037
'If you do,'
said the small pig,

26:01.081 --> 26:03.431
'don't call us,
we'll call you.'

26:03.474 --> 26:05.215
And he vanished so quickly,
Jenny just had time

26:05.259 --> 26:07.304
to snatch the last sandwich.

26:07.348 --> 26:09.480
It was salami, her favorite."

26:11.352 --> 26:13.746
[soft guitar]

26:19.229 --> 26:22.319
I hope your day is
as awesome as you look.

26:22.363 --> 26:24.452
- Ah...
- [laughing]

26:24.495 --> 26:26.846
Then she said,
"Wait a minute. I got it."

26:26.889 --> 26:29.370
It's... a cross

26:29.413 --> 26:31.241
between Jimmy Buffett
and Willie Nelson.

26:31.285 --> 26:33.200
[laughing]

26:33.243 --> 26:35.463
- And there it is.
- There it is.

26:35.506 --> 26:37.465
I don't want
to turn your attention,

26:37.508 --> 26:39.641
but there's a beautiful woman
standing at the door.

26:39.685 --> 26:41.643
Ah, Tamara.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.123
- Okay, see you later.
- Tamara?

26:43.166 --> 26:44.864
I'll see you... Tamara.

26:44.907 --> 26:46.300
[laughing]

26:48.563 --> 26:50.521
One of the pleasures
of my life

26:50.565 --> 26:52.219
is to turn around
and see a woman

26:52.262 --> 26:54.177
hold something up
and have her put

26:54.221 --> 26:56.397
her thumb up and say yes.

26:56.440 --> 26:58.442
- [laughing]
- You know,

26:58.486 --> 27:01.141
- if this was my life?
- Yeah, simple pleasures.

27:01.184 --> 27:03.012
[laughing]

27:03.056 --> 27:04.623
"My heart being hungry
feeds on food,

27:04.666 --> 27:07.364
the fat of... heart despised.

27:07.408 --> 27:08.801
Beauty where
beauty never stood.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.367
And sweet
where no sweet lies.

27:10.411 --> 27:12.108
- I gather to my..."
- [phone ringing]

27:12.152 --> 27:14.154
"...querulous needs, having
a growing heart to feed."

